    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "dcda2a00e8bd2599",
      "text": "> The [https://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/ukgwa/20080821071133/http://www.designcouncil.org.uk/en/About-Design/managingdesign/The-Study-of-the-Design-Process/ ‘Double Diamond’] process maps the divergent and convergent stages of a design process. Created by [https://www.designcouncil.org.uk/ The British Design Council], it describes modes of thinking that designers use. The Council’s origin is Industrial Design – which is about creating tangible objects. As such, the model seems like a linear process. It describes significant up-front design, before going on to produce a final solution. Working this way means that solutions are generally perfected before public release. That’s because it’s expensive to change a physical product after it has shipped. Another effect is that a lot of time passes before knowing it’s efficacy in a real market."
